.el .ds Aq '
.TH nixling 1 1970-01-01 "nixling 0.0.0-bootstrap" "nixling CLI"
.SH NAME
nixling \- nixling — opinionated NixOS desktop microVM CLI.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBnixling\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
nixling — daemon\-native CLI for nixling microVMs.
.PP
All mutating verbs dispatch through nixlingd and nixling\-priv\-broker. Read\-only verbs (list, status, audit, host check) query the daemon or the static manifest. See `nixling <COMMAND> \-\-help` for per\-verb usage.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
nixling\-list(1)
List declared VMs from the static manifest
.TP
nixling\-status(1)
Show per\-VM runtime status plus bridge health
.TP
nixling\-usb(1)
USBIP attach / detach / probe
.TP
nixling\-console(1)
Foreground serial console bridge for headless VMs (not yet implemented)
.TP
nixling\-audio(1)
Per\-VM audio grant bridge (not yet implemented)
.TP
nixling\-audit(1)
Tail the broker audit log
.TP
nixling\-host(1)
Host\-side preflight, install, doctor, and reconcile verbs
.TP
nixling\-auth(1)
Authorisation introspection
.TP
nixling\-vm(1)
Per\-VM lifecycle verbs (start / stop / restart / list / status / konsole)
.TP
nixling\-up(1)
Alias for `vm start <vm>`
.TP
nixling\-down(1)
Alias for `vm stop <vm>`
.TP
nixling\-restart(1)
Alias for `vm restart <vm>`
.TP
nixling\-build(1)
Non\-destructive eval + build of the per\-VM toplevel
.TP
nixling\-generations(1)
List current / booted / numbered generations for a VM
.TP
nixling\-switch(1)
Atomically activate a new per\-VM closure
.TP
nixling\-boot(1)
Stage a per\-VM closure for the next boot only
.TP
nixling\-test(1)
Activate a per\-VM closure with rollback on reboot
.TP
nixling\-rollback(1)
Roll a VM back to its previous generation
.TP
nixling\-gc(1)
Garbage\-collect the per\-VM /nix/store hardlink farm
.TP
nixling\-keys(1)
Managed\-key lifecycle (list / show / rotate)
.TP
nixling\-trust(1)
Trust a VM\*(Aqs host key on first use (TOFU)
.TP
nixling\-rotate\-known\-host(1)
Rotate the consumer\*(Aqs recorded known\-host entry for a VM
.TP
nixling\-migrate(1)
Analyse the host config and emit a migration plan
.TP
nixling\-config(1)
Sync / review / approve a VM\*(Aqs guest\-editable config (`guestConfigFile`): pull the operator\*(Aqs in\-VM edits to a host\-side staging file, diff them, and approve them
.TP
nixling\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.0.0\-bootstrap
